a.title: ― Member: Element in a collection that can be either atomic (individual member) or composite (collection).
a.xlink:title: ― Member: Element in a collection that can be either atomic (individual member) or composite (collection).

a.title: ― Structure: Organized set of relationships between members in a collection. a.title: ― StatisticalClassificationRelationship: Specifies the statistical classifications for the source and target of a complex relationship and defines the relationship.
a.xlink:title: ― StatisticalClassificationRelationship: Specifies the statistical classifications for the source and target of a complex relationship and defines the relationship.

a.title: ― AgentRelationship: Defines the relation of an agent within a structure.
a.xlink:title: ― AgentRelationship: Defines the relation of an agent within a structure.

a.title: ― VariableRelationship: Relationship between any variables in the variable cascade (conceptual, represented, instance), based on an ordered relation.
a.xlink:title: ― VariableRelationship: Relationship between any variables in the variable cascade (conceptual, represented, instance), based on an ordered relation.

a.title: ― CodeRelationship: Source target relationship between codes in a code relation structure.
a.xlink:title: ― CodeRelationship: Source target relationship between codes in a code relation structure.

a.title: ― ConceptRelationship: Relationship between a pair of concepts in a collection of concepts. Use controlled vocabulary provided in semantics to identify the type of relationship (relation, e.g. ParentChild, WholePart, etc.)

a.title: ― ClassificationItemRelationship: Source-target relationship between classification items in a classification item relation structure.

a.title: ― PhysicalRecordSegmentRelationship: Structured relationship between physical record segments.

a.title: ― ValueMappingRelationship: Relationships among data points in a physical layout.
a.xlink:title: ― ValueMappingRelationship: Relationships among data points in a physical layout.

a.title: ― CategoryRelationship: Source-to-target relationship between categories in a structure.
a.xlink:title: ― CategoryRelationship: Source-to-target relationship between categories in a structure.

a.title: ― DataPointRelationship: Relations used by the data point relation structure of a logical record to describe specific source-target data points and their relationship.
